un","usage":"bekah(1x)"},"H1236":{"id":"H1236","lemma":"בִּקְעָא","translit":"biqʻâʼ","pron":"bik-aw'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1237 (בִּקְעָה)","strongs_def":"{properly, a split, i.e. a wide level valley between mountains}","kjv_def":"plain.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"plain(1x)"},"H1237":{"id":"H1237","lemma":"בִּקְעָה","translit":"biqʻâh","pron":"bik-aw'","derivation":"from H1234 (בָּקַע);","strongs_def":"properly, a split, i.e. a wide level valley between mountains","kjv_def":"plain, valley.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"valley(13x), plain(7x)"},"H1238":{"id":"H1238","lemma":"בָּקַק","translit":"bâqaq","pron":"baw-kah'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to pour out, i.e. to empty, figuratively, to depopulate; by analogy, to spread out (as a fruitful vine)","kjv_def":"(make) empty (out), fail, [idiom] utterly, make void.","pos":"verb","usage":"empty(5x), emptiers(1x), fail(1x)"},"H1239":{"id":"H1239","lemma":"בָּקַר","translit":"bâqar","pron":"baw-kar","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to plough, or (generally) break forth, i.e. (figuratively) to inspect, admire, care for, consider","kjv_def":"(make) inquire (-ry), (make) search, seek out.","pos":"verb","usage":"enquire(3x), seek(3x), search(1x)"},"H1240":{"id":"H1240","lemma":"בְּקַר","translit":"bᵉqar","pron":"bek-ar'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1239 (בָּקַר)","strongs_def":"{properly, to plough, or (generally) break forth, i.e. (figuratively) to inspect, admire, care for, consider}","kjv_def":"inquire, make search.","pos":"verb","usage":"enquire(1x)"},"H1241":{"id":"H1241","lemma":"בָּקָר","translit":"bâqâr","pron":"baw-kawr'","derivation":"from H1239 (בָּקַר);","strongs_def":"beef cattle or an animal of the ox family of either gender (as used for plowing); collectively, a herd","kjv_def":"beeve, bull ([phrase] -ock), [phrase] calf, [phrase] cow, great (cattle), [phrase] heifer, herd, kine, ox.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"ox(78x),