om H1247 (בַּר);","strongs_def":"the heir (apparent to the throne)","kjv_def":"son.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"son(4x)"},"H1249":{"id":"H1249","lemma":"בַּר","translit":"bar","pron":"bar","derivation":"from H1305 (בָּרַר) (in its various senses);","strongs_def":"beloved; also pure, empty","kjv_def":"choice, clean, clear, pure.","pos":"adjective, adverb","usage":"clean(3x), pure(2x), choice(1x), clear(1x)"},"H1250":{"id":"H1250","lemma":"בָּר","translit":"bâr","pron":"bawr","derivation":"or בַּר; from H1305 (בָּרַר) (in the sense of winnowing);","strongs_def":"grain of any kind (even while standing in the field); by extension the open country","kjv_def":"corn, wheat.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"corn(9x), wheat(5x)"},"H1251":{"id":"H1251","lemma":"בַּר","translit":"bar","pron":"bar","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1250 (בָּר);","strongs_def":"a field","kjv_def":"field.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"field(8x)"},"H1252":{"id":"H1252","lemma":"בֹּר","translit":"bôr","pron":"bore","derivation":"from H1305 (בָּרַר);","strongs_def":"purify","kjv_def":"cleanness, pureness.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"cleanness(4x), pureness(1x), never(1x)"},"H1253":{"id":"H1253","lemma":"בֹּר","translit":"bôr","pron":"bore","derivation":"the same as H1252 (בֹּר);","strongs_def":"vegetable lye (from its cleansing); used as a soap forwashing, or a flux formetals","kjv_def":"[idiom] never so, purely.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"purely(1x)"},"H1254":{"id":"H1254","lemma":"בָּרָא","translit":"bârâʼ","pron":"baw-raw'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"(absolutely) to create; (qualified) to cut down (a wood), select, feed (as formative processes)","kjv_def":"choose, create (creator), cut down, dispatch, do, make (fat).","pos":"verb","usage":"create(42x), creator(3x), choose(2x), make(2x), dispatch(1x), done(1x)"},"H1255":{"id":"H1255","lemma":"בְּרֹאדַךְ בַּלְאֲדָן","translit":"Bᵉrôʼdak Balʼădân","pron":"ber-o-dak' bal-ad-awn'","derivation":"a variation of H4757 (מְרֹאדַךְ בַּלְאָדָן);","strongs_def":"Berodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king","kjv_def":"Berodach-baladan.Birliy."},"H1256":{"id":"H1256","lemma":"בְּרָאיָה","translit":"Bᵉrâʼyâh","pron":"ber-aw-yaw'","derivation":"from H1254 (בָּרָא) and H8050 (שְׁמוּאֵל); Jah has created;","strongs_def":"Berajah, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Beraiah."},"H1257":{"id":"H1257","lemma":"בַּרְבֻּר","translit":"barbur","pron":"bar-boor'","derivation":"by reduplication from H1250 (בָּר);","strongs_def":"a fowl (as fattened on grain)","kjv_def":"fowl."},"H1258":{"id":"H1258","lemma":"בָּרַד","translit":"bârad","pron":"baw-rad'","derivation":"a primitive root,","strongs_def":"to hail","kjv_def":"hail.","pos":"denominative verb"},"H1259":{"id":"H1259","lemma":"בָּרָד","translit":"bârâd","pron":"baw-rawd'","derivation":"from H1258 (בָּרַד);","strongs_def":"hail","kjv_def":"hail(stones).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"hail(27x)"},"H1260":{"id":"H1260","lemma":"בֶּרֶד","translit":"Bered","pron":"beh'red","derivation":"from H1258 (בָּרַד); hail;","strongs_def":"Bered, the name of a place south of Palestine, also of an Israelite","kjv_def":"Bered."},"H1261":{"id":"H1261","lemma":"בָּרֹד","translit":"bârôd","pron":"baw-rode'","derivation":"from H1258 (בָּרַד);","strongs_def":"spotted (as if with hail)","kjv_def":"grisled.","pos":"adjective","usage":"grisled(4x)"},"H1262":{"id":"H1262","lemma":"בָּרָה","translit":"bârâh","pron":"baw-raw'","derivation":"a primitive root; to select; also (as denominative from H1250 (בָּר)) to feed; also (as equivalent to H1305 (בָּרַר)) to render clear (Ecclesiastes 3:18)","strongs_def":"to select; to feed; to render clear","kjv_def":"choose, (cause to) eat, manifest, (give) meat.","pos":"verb","usage":"eat(4x), choose(1x), give(1x)"},"H1263":{"id":"H1263","lemma":"בָּרוּךְ","translit":"Bârûwk","pron":"baw-rook'","derivation":"passive participle from H1288 (בָרַךְ); blessed;","strongs_def":"Baruk, the name of three Israelites","kjv_def":"Baruch.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Baruch(26x)"},"H1264":{"id":"H1264","lemma":"בְּרוֹם","translit":"bᵉrôwm","pron":"ber-ome'","derivation":"probably of foreign origin;","strongs_def":"damask (stuff of variegated thread)","kjv_def":"rich apparel.","pos":"masculine noun"},"H1265":{"id":"H1265","lemma":"בְּרוֹשׁ","translit":"bᵉrôwsh","pron":"ber-osh'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a cypress (?) tree; hence, a lance or a musical instrument (as made of that wood)","kjv_def":"fir (tree).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"fir(7x)"},"H1266":{"id":"H1266","lemma":"בְּרוֹת","translit":"bᵉrôwth","pron":"ber-oth'","derivation":"a variation of H1265 (בְּרוֹשׁ);","strongs_def":"the cypress (or some elastic tree)","kjv_def":"fir."},"H1267":{"id":"H1267","lemma":"בָּרוּת","translit":"bârûwth","pron":"baw-rooth","derivation":"from H1262 (בָּרָה);","strongs_def":"food","kjv_def":"meat.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"meat(1x)"},"H1268":{"id":"H1268","lemma":"בֵּרוֹתָה","translit":"Bêrôwthâh","pron":"bay-ro-thaw'","derivation":"or בֵּרֹתַי; probably from H1266 (בְּרוֹת)lemma בֻּרוֹת first vowel, corrected to בְּרוֹת; cypress or cypresslike;","strongs_def":"Berothah or Berothai, a place north of Palestine","kjv_def":"Berothah, Berothai.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Berothah(1x), Berothai(1x)"},"H1269":{"id":"H1269","lemma":"בִּרְזוֹת","translit":"Birzôwth","pron":"beer-zoth'","derivation":"probably feminine plural from an unused root (apparently mean to pierce); holes;","strongs_def":"Birzoth, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Birzavith (from the marg.)."},"H1270":{"id":"H1270","lemma":"בַּרְזֶל","translit":"barzel","pron":"bar-zel'","derivation":"perhaps from the root of H1269 (בִּרְזוֹת);","strongs_def":"iron (as cutting); by extension, an iron implement","kjv_def":"(ax) head, iron.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"iron(73x)"},"H1271":{"id":"H1271","lemma":"בַּרְזִלַּי","translit":"Barzillay","pron":"bar-zil-lah'-ee","derivation":"from H1270 (בַּרְזֶל); iron-hearte