enediction; by implication prosperity","kjv_def":"blessing, liberal, pool, present.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"blessing(61x), blessed(3x), present(3x), liberal(1x), pools(1x)"},"H1294":{"id":"H1294","lemma":"בְּרָכָה","translit":"Bᵉrâkâh","pron":"ber-aw-kaw'","derivation":"the same as H1293 (בְּרָכָה);","strongs_def":"Berakah, the name of an Israelite, and also of a valley in Palestine","kjv_def":"Berachah."},"H1295":{"id":"H1295","lemma":"בְּרֵכָה","translit":"bᵉrêkâh","pron":"ber-ay-kaw'","derivation":"from H1288 (בָרַךְ);","strongs_def":"a reservoir (at which camels kneel as a resting-place)","kjv_def":"(fish-) pool.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"pool(16x), fishpools(1x)"},"H1296":{"id":"H1296","lemma":"בֶּרֶכְיָה","translit":"Berekyâh","pron":"beh-rek-yaw'","derivation":"or בֶּרֶכְיָהוּ; from H1290 (בֶּרֶךְ) and H3050 (יָהּ); knee (i.e. blessing) of Jah;","strongs_def":"Berekjah, the name of six Israelites","kjv_def":"Berachiah, Berechiah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Berechiah(10x), Berachiah(1x)"},"H1297":{"id":"H1297","lemma":"בְּרַם","translit":"bᵉram","pron":"ber-am'","derivation":"(Aramaic) perhaps from H7313 (רוּם) with a prepositional prefix;","strongs_def":"properly, highly, i.e. surely; but used adversatively, however","kjv_def":"but, nevertheless, yet.","pos":"adverb","usage":"but(2x), yet(2x), nevertheless(1x)"},"H1298":{"id":"H1298","lemma":"בֶּרַע","translit":"Beraʻ","pron":"beh'-rah","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Bera, a Sodomitish king","kjv_def":"Bera.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Bera(1x)"},"H1299":{"id":"H1299","lemma":"בָּרַק","translit":"bâraq","pron":"baw-rak'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to lighten (lightning)","kjv_def":"cast forth.","pos":"verb"}}